correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and non-compliant with the schema, with many values ungrounded or null and several schema violations. Key issues: 1) Schema violations: numerous fields that require numbers contain nulls (pressure.quantityValue.numericValue; thicknessControl.growthPerCycle.values[*].value.quantityValue.numericValue; thicknessControl.numberofCycles.quantityValue.numericValue; nucleationPeriod.quantityValue.numericValue; dosingTime[*].precursor/coReactant.quantityValue.numericValue; purgeTime[*].precursor/coReactant.quantityValue.numericValue; flowRates[*].precursorFlow/coReactantFlow/purgingGasFlow.quantityValue.numericValue; materialProperties.uniformity.variation.quantityValue.numericValue; conformality.aspectRatio.quantityValue.numericValue; filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue; roughness.value.quantityValue.numericValue; filmDensity.value.quantityValue.numericValue; deviceProperties.onOffRatio.quantityValue.numericValue). Also, processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null although the property, if present, must be an object; for thermal ALD it should be omitted. 2) Ungrounded or incorrect values: reactantSelection lists specific precursors (DEZn, TMGa, an “In(Ga) bimetallic precursor”) and O3 as co-reactant without any support in the article; carrier/purge gas set to N2 is not stated; substrate simplified to “SiO2/Si substrates” whereas the article uses a complex OT stack on 300 mm wafers; temperature fixed at 200°C though only a range 200–300°C is reported; supercycle sequence/counts not provided in the paper; saturation=False is assumed with no support; crystallinity set to amorphous without explicit experimental confirmation; filmComposition.atomicRatio=value “Not Found” instead of the reported metal ratios (e.g., In0.17Ga0.45Zn0.38 by XRF); otherAspects.filmStability=False contradicts the article (In-poor IGZO shows high stability under FGA and reduced H-induced PBTI); reproducibility=False is unjustified given multiple devices per composition and concurrent stressing. 3) Missing processes: the paper reports six IGZO compositions deposited by ALD; only one process instance is extracted. 4) Partial correctness: filmThickness=7 nm and deviceProperties for the In0.17Ga0.45Zn0.38 sample (μ≈8 cm^2/Vs, V_TH≈0.3 V, SS≈94 mV/dec) align with the text, and ALD method being thermal is correct; ALD temperature range (200–300°C) and supercycle concept (2–9 sub-cycles per binary oxide) are stated in SI but were not properly captured. Properties to correct/review: remove nulls and either provide grounded numeric values or omit optional blocks; delete plasmaPower or provide a valid object only if PEALD; replace unsubstantiated precursors/co-reactant/gases with values supported by the article (or leave out if schema allows); set temperature to reported range or a specific value if stated; provide filmComposition (e.g., In:Ga:Zn = 0.17:0.45:0.38, method XRF); set otherAspects.filmStability to true for In-poor IGZO; add separate process instances for each reported composition; ensure all required fields contain valid, QUDT-compliant values traceable to the text.

completeness.rationale: Major incompleteness and weak traceability. (1) Multiple processes not captured: the article reports ALD IGZO channels with six distinct compositions (Table 1) and a consistent 7 nm thickness, but only a single IGZO ALD process is extracted. Each composition should be represented as a separate IGZO ALD supercycle process (and, if within scope, distinct temperature ranges between 200–300 °C per recipe). (2) Numerous schema fields are null or placeholders, violating the no-empty requirement: pressure, growth-per-cycle values, number of cycles, nucleation period, dosing times, purge times, flow rates, supercycle subcycle counts, optical/electrical/uniformity/conformality/roughness/density metrics, on/off ratio all contain null or 'Not Found'. (3) Unsubstantiated reactant details: precursors (DEZn, TMGa, “In(Ga) bimetallic precursor”) and oxidant O3, carrier/purge gas N2 are not reported in the paper/Supporting Information; these must be removed or replaced with traceable values. (4) Supercycle design incomplete: the SI states a nanolaminate supercycle with 2–9 cycles per sub-cycle; extracted ‘numberofSubcycles’ has null counts and lacks the a:b:c ratio per composition. (5) Process parameters inaccurate/underspecified: temperature is given as a single 200 °C value whereas the SI states 200–300 °C; substrate is simplified (“SiO2/Si”) despite the OT stack; plasmaPower is present but null even though TALD (thermal) implies not applicable. (6) Material properties and composition missing: atomic ratios for each composition (e.g., In0.17:Ga0.45:Zn0.38) should be populated and tied to XRF; crystallinity set to ‘amorphous’ is not explicitly stated; many required materialProperties entries are empty. (7) Device properties partially captured but not consistently linked to the corresponding composition/process; on/off ratio is missing though performance data are discussed; filmStability/reproducibility marked False without support and contradict stability claims for In-poor films. To improve: add one IGZO ALD process per composition (with 7 nm film thickness), populate supercycle a:b:c counts consistent with compositions, provide deposition temperature range, remove speculative precursors/oxidant/gases or cite them if present, fill required timing/flow/pressure/GPC/number of cycles or mark not reported by omitting optional fields, supply XRF-based atomic ratios and link device metrics to the correct composition, and avoid null/placeholder values.
